ce:section.ce:para:
The crystallinity (X2/X1) and average crystallite size (Da2
                     / Da1
                     ) of the porous Pd/Cdot nanoparticles were 1.14 and 2.04 times higher than the crystallinity and average crystallite size, respectively, of the non-porous Pd/Cdot nanoparticles. This higher crystallinity and average crystallite size positively enhanced the electrocatalytic activities of the porous Pd/Cdot nanoparticles, agreeing with the findings of Meng et al. and Lima et al. [31,32]. The methane adsorption (VL) and kinetics of the CO oxidation displayed an exponential increase with the increasing crystallite size of the nanoparticles.
